A TV sketch show that likens Margaret Thatcher to fictional serial killer Hannibal Lecter and depicts the Queen Mother as a foul-mouthed drunk has been branded ‘hideous’, ‘savage’ and ‘beyond the acceptable bounds of satire’.

Historian Andrew Roberts, former Minister John Redwood and Royal biographer Penny Junor are among those who have condemned the comedy series Psychobitches.

In one sequence, Lady Thatcher – played by Doctor Who star Michelle Gomez – vomits at the suggestion that every human being has an innate value. 

