Friends of Lady Thatcher last night described the portrayal of the former Tory leader, who died last year, as upsetting to both her family and everyone who voted for her.

Mr Roberts, a trustee of The Margaret Thatcher Archive Trust, said: ‘Margaret Thatcher was used to being traduced throughout her life and was never affected by it. 

'But the sheer savagery of this goes beyond the acceptable bounds of satire.’

Tory MP Mr Redwood said: ‘I think this depiction would have been hurtful to her if she was still alive and it is certainly hurtful to her family and to the rest of us who supported her.’

Royal biographer Ms Junor said the portrayal of the Queen Mother was untrue. She added: ‘This sounds hideous to me and not remotely funny or even remotely true. I just think it’s nasty.’

 

